I’m just over here journaling and sitting with myself.  I’m a compulsive self-helper and I’m trying to not do ALL the therapies and do everything “right” for once and just accept things as they are and as they come. It’s hard being a “fixer” and having this insatiable need to fix everything, to do everything right. And have it all happen NOW NOW NOW. The word that keeps coming up in meditations is: patience. Something I honestly know nothing about. I feel like a child grasping at the most rudimentary ideas… “patience”. This concept has not been a part of my life… ever. I can’t even let paint dry. While my drive to complete and finish things suits me in work just fine, it rarely serves my soul. I think a fundamental aspect of patience is Trust. Trusting that the answers will come, trusting that this time serves a purpose, trusting that I will learn what I need to in order to break cycles and heal.  Trust and Patience, woof! Who knew that would be my Achilles Heel.

@nataliefalt and I loved working with @depict33 on these @miguel Viscera event fixtures. The merch display was so enticing and the mantra vocal booth crates were exactly how we designed them. It’s amazing when someone builds something that looks exactly like your renderings. Shoutout to @daniellioooo and @tashaclub for their epic merchandising skills and @omdigital for making the mantra experience so special that people did it twice in a row! And also @stuffed_by_carly for upholstering our padded little experience.

Sometimes simple really is better. PDs, photographers, directors, CDs all know that there’s a lot of decisions, conversations, and work that happens in order to remove everything superfluous to ensure the art [artist] stand out.  The team did an epic job nailing this one.

I absolutely adored working with @tonestith. His kindness, raw talent and work ethic made our job so effortless. I’m so happy I get to work with such wonderful people.

King Leonidas Mohon: you were a fierce warrior and the most beautiful in all of the land. Thank you for choosing @rory_khan_mohon and I during your time here on earth. May you nap in endless fields, lay siege upon many a chicken coop, may you smell all the smells and feel the air blowing across your face till you’ve had your fill. May you find fries and slices of pizza on the ground wherever your journey takes you. But most of all I hope you find the wild freedom you always longed for. I’ll see you on the other side my sweet Leo.
A little #shelfie. I love the bold and elegant design of this @georgjensen French Press.

Anyone who knows me or works with me knows that the color RED is my go-to solution for most things. (We need this Elegant? RED! We need this young and bold? RED! We need this to pop? RED! We need this to be iconic? RED!) I think I get it from my mother who had an amazing red phase in the 90s. I get most of my good traits from her so that makes sense. Right, mom?
